# 🔵 Blue Team — Defensive Setup

## Defense Summary

In this project, the blue team designed and implemented a multi-layered defensive environment across multiple virtual machines to simulate a realistic enterprise network. We deployed Wazuh as our centralized SIEM to aggregate, correlate, and analyze security events, providing real-time visibility into system and network activity. To strengthen network-based threat detection, we integrated both Snort and Suricata as IDS solutions. We also developed a comprehensive custom Snort ruleset tailored to our lab environment, which streamlined alert categorization and improved log readability when ingested into Wazuh.

---

## Wazuh SIEM

### Installation

We installed Wazuh on the SIEM VM using the quickstart installation script from the Wazuh website:

```bash
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.14/wazuh-install.sh && sudo bash ./wazuh-install.sh -a
```

This installs all 3 components of Wazuh: the **indexer**, **manager**, and **dashboard**. After installation, admin credentials are displayed — make sure to save these for dashboard login.

![Wazuh Dashboard](../screenshots/blue-team/wazuh-dashboard.png)
*Wazuh SIEM dashboard displaying correlated alerts*

### Agent Installation

To install agents on other VMs, navigate to **Deploy New Agents** on the Wazuh dashboard and fill out the agent information. Copy the generated command and paste it into the target VM's terminal. Then enable and start the agent:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable wazuh-agent
sudo systemctl start wazuh-agent
```

![Active Agents](../screenshots/blue-team/wazuh-agents.png)
*All agents successfully connected and active in Wazuh*

### Custom Snort Rules

We created a custom `snort3_rules.xml` file on the Wazuh Manager VM with rules tailored to our environment. Each rule has a specific description based on the attack type and a severity level:

```xml
<group name="snort,">
  <rule id="100200" level="6">
    <decoded_as>snort3</decoded_as>
    <description>Snort3 IDS alert detected</description>
  </rule>
  <rule id="100202" level="12">
    <if_sid>100201</if_sid>
    <match>port_scan</match>
    <description>Snort3: Port scan from attacker VM 192.168.100.20</description>
  </rule>
</group>
```

> Full rules file: [snort3_rules.xml](../rules/snort3_rules.xml)

![Snort Rules Alert](../screenshots/blue-team/snort-alerts.png)
*Successful port scan alert captured by Snort and displayed in Wazuh*

