## Suricata (NIDS)

### Installation

```bash
sudo apt install suricata -y
```

### Configuration

Edit the Suricata config file to set your network and interface:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
```

Key settings to update:
- Set `HOME_NET` to your LAN subnet: `[192.168.100.0/24]`
- Set the interface under `af-packet` to match your bridged adapter (e.g. `enp0s8`)

![Suricata Config](../screenshots/blue-team/suricata-config.png)
*suricata.yaml showing HOME_NET and interface configuration*

### Validate Configuration

```bash
suricata -T -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
```

You should see a `Configuration provided was successfully loaded` message.

### Custom ICMP Rule

We created a custom rule to detect any ICMP ping to the agent VM:

```
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ICMP Ping Detected"; sid:1; rev:1;)
```

Add this to `/var/lib/suricata/rules/local.rules` and reference it in the yaml rules-files section.

### Wazuh Integration

In the Wazuh agent `ossec.conf` file, add the Suricata log path with JSON format:

```xml
<localfile>
  <log_format>json</log_format>
  <location>/var/log/suricata/eve.json</location>
</localfile>
```

Restart both Suricata and the Wazuh agent after making changes.

![Suricata Alerts in Wazuh](../screenshots/blue-team/suricata-alerts.png)
*Suricata alerts successfully forwarded to the Wazuh SIEM dashboard*

