## Snort 3 (IDS/IPS)

### Installation

Snort 3 was compiled from source on the Ubuntu Server VM. We first installed all dependencies, then installed LibDAQ, and finally compiled and installed Snort 3.

![Snort Installation](../screenshots/blue-team/snort-install.png)
*Successful installation of LibDAQ and Snort 3*

### Configuration

We configured `snort.lua` with the community rules (8,496 rules loaded) and enabled `alert_fast` output logging:

```lua
alert_fast =
{
    file = true,
    packet = false,
    limit = 10,
}
```

![Snort Rules Validation](../screenshots/blue-team/snort-rules.png)
*Validation of 8,496 pre-configured community rules*

### Running as a Service

We configured Snort 3 to start automatically on boot using systemd:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/snort3.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Snort3 NIDS
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/snort -c /usr/local/etc/snort/snort.lua -i enp0s3 -A alert_fast -l /var/log/snort
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable snort3
sudo systemctl start snort3
```

### Wazuh Integration

We installed the Wazuh agent on the Snort Server and configured it to read the Snort alert file:

```xml
<localfile>
  <log_format>snort-fast</log_format>
  <location>/var/log/snort/alert_fast.txt</location>
</localfile>
```

We also created a custom decoder on the Wazuh Manager VM:

```xml
<decoder name="snort3">
  <prematch>[**]</prematch>
</decoder>
```

![Snort Alert in Wazuh](../screenshots/blue-team/snort-wazuh.png)
*Successful Snort port scan alert forwarded and displayed in Wazuh*
